.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "December 2023" "Simple Shell 1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A basic shell program

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBsimple_shell\fP program is a basic shell that allows users to enter commands and executes them. It supports
interactive mode and provides a prompt for user input. The shell also includes a built-in "exit" command to
terminate the program.


.SH COMMANDS
The \fBsimple_shell\fP supports the following built-in command:

.TP
\fBexit\fP
Exits the shell.

.SH USAGE
Run the \fBsimple_shell\fP program without any arguments.

.B
$ ./hsh

.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
In interactive mode, the shell displays a prompt and waits for user input. Commands entered by the user are
executed until the user enters the "exit" command.

.SH EXAMPLES
To run the \fBsimple_shell\fP program:

.B
$ simple_shell

This will start the shell in interactive mode. You can then enter commands, and the shell will execute them.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The \fBsimple_shell\fP program returns 0 upon successful execution.

